cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and dynamic provisioning of network services, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the deployment of virtualized network functions (VNFs) to commodity servers in cloud datacenters, which is related to distributed and cluster computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes online algorithms for dynamic provisioning of VNFs, which can be considered as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper designs efficient online algorithms for VNF scaling, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses theoretical analysis to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithms, which is related to information theory.
